00:39:44.929 --> 00:39:52.489
You should not give your daughters their sons, nor accept any of their daughters for your sons.

00:39:52.489 --> 00:39:59.489
You have to file the priesthood. You may not serve as a priest, nor remain in Jerusalem.

00:39:59.489 --> 00:40:05.489
It took some time, but true worship was restored.

00:40:05.489 --> 00:40:13.289
Nehemiah didn't walk away, did he?

00:40:13.289 --> 00:40:17.289
No, he persevered in his assignment. Why?

00:40:17.289 --> 00:40:21.289
Because he held on to his joy.

00:40:21.289 --> 00:40:27.289
You see, his main source of joy came not from his accomplishments,

00:40:27.289 --> 00:40:33.289
not from the security of walls, nor even from what others were doing.

00:40:33.289 --> 00:40:37.289
From where does true joy come?

00:40:37.289 --> 00:40:45.289
Nehemiah himself told us, the joy of Jehovah is your stronghold.

00:40:45.289 --> 00:40:48.289
So here's lesson number three for us.

00:40:48.289 --> 00:40:57.289
Despite challenges and setbacks, we can be joyful because true joy comes from a good relationship with Jehovah.

00:40:57.289 --> 00:41:01.289
Nehemiah was a man like you and me.

00:41:01.289 --> 00:41:08.289
Remember, he didn't have Jehovah's power displayed supernaturally to him like Moses and Joshua did.

00:41:08.289 --> 00:41:17.289
But what did he have? He had prayer. He had faith. And he had trust.

00:41:17.289 --> 00:41:24.289
Those were his tools. And there's no doubt that Jehovah was active on behalf of Nehemiah,

00:41:24.289 --> 00:41:27.289
guiding and blessing his efforts.

00:41:27.289 --> 00:41:34.289
We have those same tools today. Pray to Jehovah, put faith in him,

00:41:34.289 --> 00:41:38.289
and trust that he will bless yourself sacrificing efforts,

00:41:38.289 --> 00:41:44.289
just as Jehovah gave Nehemiah the courage, the energy, the insight,

00:41:44.289 --> 00:41:50.289
and the perseverance to carry out his assignment, he'll do the same for you.
